content.description:
A nice line to do if in the area and serves as the only warm up on the wall. Mentioned in the Bloom guide as "Thin hands and stemming..." but seems to be mostly lacking of those qualities.  

  Leave veg-ledge through steep but moderate intro moves. Gain splitter crack in a clean corner. Pull through steepening features to a break in difficulty. Move up left through broken and fun terrain to top block.
content.location: Climbs twenty or so feet climbers right of Fluke or Flounder. Starts on nice sized veg-ledge with a large Juniper standing near by. Look for clean splitter in a corner.

content.description: Fluke or Flounder is a nice little route that would deserve another star if it weren't for the chossy start.  This is the most obvious line of the two or three at this wall.  Climb up some junky rock with not so good pro to a stance.  Step hard right and work up a great finger crack to the top.
This is a small wall that is located between the Obscenity Wall and White Wall.
